2. Increase in real wages of British workers.
3. Government subsidies and policies stabilizing food prices.
4. Global trade agreements and imports increasing competition.
5. Expansion of supermarkets and large retail chains driving down costs.
6. Technological advancements in food production and preservation reducing waste and costs.

Analysis:
